<dl id="s14041d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14041d">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s14all.htm#s14041d">sector 41(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> bonze <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="s14041d"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/lexp.htm#s14041d">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/p86.htm#s14041d">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/p86.htm#s14041d">1986 (14.674)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/l22p.htm#s14041d">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#s14041d">MS V.A.17-0v</ms> </li><li>JJA 14:098 </li><li><a name="p12d" href="../udra/u14da.htm#p12d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/p12d.htm#s14041d">Draft: 14.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">In every country, my friend, the <mark>bonzes</mark>, the brachmans, and the priests, deceive the people; all reformations begin from the laity; the priests point us out the way to heaven with their fingers, but stand still themselves, nor seem to travel towards the country in view. <small> Oliver Goldsmith, <a name="OGCW" href="/udra/udex.htm#OGCW"><cite title="source">Complete Works</cite></a> (n.d), <i>Citizen of the World</i>, p 417</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
